---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Nicaragua Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/nicaragua/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Costa Rica for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/costa-rica' },
  { title: 'Panama for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/panama' },
  { title: 'Guatemala for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/guatemala' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'nicaraguaFit', header: 'Nicaragua Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$320-460/mo', nicaraguaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$375-535/mo', nicaraguaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$290-420/mo', nicaraguaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'To 80', monthlyFrom: '$260-375/mo', nicaraguaFit: 'Good' },
  { provider: 'Nicaraguan Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: '$60-180/mo', nicaraguaFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$290-460', annual: '$3,480-5,520' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$400-600', annual: '$4,800-7,200' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$540-810', annual: '$6,480-9,720' },
  { category: 'Nicaragua Private Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: '$25-70/visit' },
  { category: 'Nicaragua Public', monthly: 'Free/nominal', annual: 'Basic quality' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Nicaragua 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Nicaragua. Colonial Granada, volcanoes, extremely affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Nicaragua"
  subheadline="Nicaragua offers colonial Granada charm, volcanic landscapes, extremely affordable living, and famous pensionado benefits—Central America most affordable retirement destination."
  heroImage="/images/countries/nicaragua-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Nicaragua</h2>
  <p>
    Nicaragua is Central America most affordable country—colonial Granada charm, volcanic Lake Nicaragua, Pacific beaches, and generous pensionado benefits. Low costs mean comfortable retirement on modest income. Political situation has stabilized.
  </p>

  <p>
    Granada offers colonial architecture on Lake Nicaragua. San Juan del Sur provides Pacific beach lifestyle with growing expat community. Managua has best healthcare but less attractive for living. Leon offers university city character. Each location offers extreme value.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Managua best</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Spanish</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> $800-1,500/month; extremely low</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Colonial; volcanic; affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Pensionado:</strong> Generous tax and import benefits</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Nicaragua Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Nicaragua healthcare is limited—concentrated in Managua. Hospital Metropolitano Vivian Pellas is best private option with modern facilities. Outside Managua, quality drops significantly. Granada and beach areas have basic clinics only.
  </p>

  <p>
    International insurance with Costa Rica or US evacuation is essential for seniors outside Managua. Many expats travel to Managua for serious care or evacuate to Costa Rica (4 hours) for complex needs.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Managua-Centric Healthcare</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Quality healthcare is concentrated in Managua—Hospital Vivian Pellas is modern. Granada is 45 minutes from Managua. San Juan del Sur and other areas require travel for serious care. Costa Rica is common evacuation destination for complex cases.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Nicaragua offers attractive pensionado benefits:
  </p>

  <h3>Pensionado Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with $600+/month guaranteed pension—one of lowest thresholds in Americas. Benefits include duty-free import of household goods and vehicle. Tax exemptions on income earned outside Nicaragua.
  </p>

  <h3>Rentista Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with investment income—demonstrate $750+/month. Similar benefits to pensionado.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    90-day visa-free for many nationalities. Extensions possible through immigration office.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Nicaragua:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pensionado visa:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Essential given limited local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Costa Rica or US evacuation critical</li>
    <li><strong>Managua access:</strong> Plan for hospital travel</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Nicaragua</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for Nicaragua seniors—local options are limited and healthcare quality varies. Plan must include Costa Rica and US evacuation. Cash payment works for routine local care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Nicaragua, international coverage with regional evacuation is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Nicaragua</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Americas network, Costa Rica/US evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Blue Cross network for US evacuation</li>
    <li><strong>IMG Global:</strong> Budget-friendly with evacuation</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with evacuation essential for Nicaragua.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Nicaragua are moderate given need for international coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Nicaraguan private care is very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Consultations $25-40; very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Americas-only:</strong> Skip worldwide coverage if not traveling globally</li>
    <li><strong>Costa Rica option:</strong> Include for quality regional care access</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Minimalist, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,100/month Social Security. Seeking maximum affordability.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Pensionado visa. Cigna Global with US evacuation. Granada living.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~$360/month. Colonial charm; extremely affordable on Social Security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Canadian Beach Couple, Both 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension CAD 2,400/month. San Juan del Sur beach lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Costa Rica accessible for complex care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~$850/month combined. Pacific beach; excellent value.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: European Adventure Seeker, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,200/month pension. Exploring volcanoes and colonial towns.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> GeoBlue with European and US coverage. Managua for healthcare.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> GeoBlue ~$330/month (~€300). Adventure lifestyle; global backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Nicaragua politically stable now?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Improved since 2018 protests. Government maintains tight control. Day-to-day life is stable for expats. Avoid political involvement. Many expats live comfortably. Monitor situation through embassy advisories.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How affordable is Nicaragua really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Extremely affordable—Central America lowest costs. Comfortable retirement possible on $800-1,200/month. Domestic help very affordable. Dining out $5-10. Rent $300-600 for decent accommodation. Extreme value for budget retirees.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is Granada like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Charming colonial city on Lake Nicaragua—oldest colonial city in Americas. Colorful architecture, good restaurants, established expat community. 45 minutes to Managua healthcare. Popular base for Nicaragua retirement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How limited is healthcare outside Managua?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very limited—basic clinics only in Granada, San Juan del Sur. Serious conditions require Managua (Hospital Vivian Pellas) or Costa Rica evacuation. Plan for travel or evacuation for significant healthcare needs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes with evacuation coverage essential for Nicaragua.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Nicaraguan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
